Bardon and Camas expected to merge - FT . British building materials firms Bardon Group Plc and Camas Plc could announce a 500 million pounds merger on Monday , the Fianncial Times newspaper said . " A link - up between the two Midlands - based groups would create one of the biggest companies in the UK aggregates industry , with combined sales of more than 725 million pounds , " the report said . The paper noted that the two had attemepted a marriage a year ago , but failed to agree a management structure . A deal now would continue the consolidation of the industry which saw market leader Tarmac Plc take over rival George Wimpey Plc ' s construction materials division last year in a swap for its housebuilding business . - - London Newsroom + 44 1717 542 7717 
